cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LM, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses the relationship between constructive and classical logic and how classical reasoning can be supported in dependent type theory. 
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the use of dependent type theory in interactive theorem provers, which is relevant to programming language design and implementation. 
3. cs.LM (Logic in Mathematics) - The paper discusses the application of classical results to constructive mathematics, which is relevant to the study of logic in mathematics. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of weak value monads to represent classical function spaces, which is relevant to information theory and data analysis. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may touch on computational complexity in the context of classical and constructive reasoning.
